main event: Two unidentified round objects were observed visually by military personnel for approximately 4 minutes.
interesting points: The first object was round and white, while the second object was round and covered in flame or fire, trailing flame.
The second object crossed the flight path of the first object a short distance behind it.
The first object disappeared over the western horizon, while the second object disappeared more slowly.
The objects were observed to be moving from east to west and north to south on straight line courses.
The sighting occurred at dawn, approximately 7 miles northwest of Keno, Oregon.
sighted object: two round objects, one white and one covered in flame/fire
